        <item>
            <key> <string>description</string> </key>
            <value> <string>Lists documents of a specific portal type with optional filtering and column selection.\n
\n
Results are paginated - each request returns at most 100 documents per page (use the \'page\' parameter starting from 0) to ensure manageable response size.\n
\n
First use MCP_listPortalTypes to discover available portal type IDs, then MCP_getPortalTypeSchema to explore columns and identify which are filterable and which appear by default.\n
\n
Results are returned in two formats:\n
1. \'content\' field: Human-readable ASCII table with columns separated by | and a header row underlined with ===. Example format:\n
\n
   COLUMN1 | COLUMN2 | COLUMN3\n
   ===========================\n
   Value1 | Value2 | Value3\n
   Value1 | Value2 | Value3\n
\n
2. \'structuredContent\' field: JSON object conforming to the outputSchema with the following structure:\n
   - count: integer - Total number of records\n
   - start: integer - Starting index of the current page\n
   - end: integer - Ending index of the current page\n
   - portal_type: string - Portal type identifier\n
   - rows: array - List of rows, each a dictionary mapping column names to values (strings, numbers, booleans, or null)\n
\n
This tool is READ-ONLY and is NON-DESTRUCTIVE.</string> </value>
        </item>
